    "Open Quest Log": "打开任务日志",
    "We’ll remember what you did.\n\nThe land to West has grown fallow, if it is of any use to you, it is yours.\n\nFurther afield, the fields could be used for farming if you could find a way to cleanse the soil.\n\nThe MycoFolk might have knowledge of such things.\n\nBut before you head West, you should seek the Desert Temple to the East, the Priest there maybe be able to help you further.": "我们会记住你所做的一切。\n\n往西边的土地已经荒芜了，不过如果这对你有用的话，那这片土地就是你的了。\n\n再往远处看，那些田地如果能清理好土壤的话就可以用来耕种了。\n\n菌裔或许有关于这类事情的知识。\n\n但在你前往西边之前，你应该先前往东边的沙漠圣殿，那里的大祭司或许能为你提供更多帮助。",
    "The old beasts don’t just guard their dens, they judge you by which you you happen to be at the moment. \n\nCome with purpose to the forest, or wander there.  \n\nThe lake listens, and you might spend a lot of time fishing there, but you might also be the kind to spend a lot of time drinking swamp sludge.  \n\nI don't judge.  \n\nSome people are a lot like ghosts, you know.  \n\nSometimes all I need to clear the ghosts is a good meal.": "那些古老的生物不仅守护着它们的巢穴，还会根据你当时的状况来评判你。 \n\n带着明确的目的来到森林，或者随意在森林里游荡。 \n\n那片湖泊在倾听，你可能会在那里花很长时间钓鱼，但也可能是个喜欢长时间喝沼泽泥浆的人。 \n\n我不评判。 \n\n有些人很像幽灵，你知道的。 \n\n有时候，我只需要一顿丰盛的美餐就能驱散那些幽灵。",
    "The elder listens gravely, then bows her head. \"We’ll send someone to sanctify what remains. We have unlocked the gate to the Foothills for you, and the land West is now yours to do with what you will.\"": "年长者神情严肃地听着，然后低下头。“我们会派人来为剩下的东西举行神圣的仪式。我们已经为你打开了通往山麓的通道，西边的土地现在归你所有，你可以随意处置。”",
    "(More town activities will appear here.)": "（更多城市活动将在这里出现）",
    "(you are paid in gold)": "（使用金币）",
    "and mark a quest as active to track it here and on the map.": "并将任务标记为活动，以便在此处和地图上跟踪它。",


    "No active quest selected": "未选择活动任务",
    "There is more work to be done to the East.\n\nI can feel it, can't you feel it?  \n\nDoes it not throb within you!?": "东方还有更多的工作要做。\n\n我能感觉到，你不能感觉到吗？\n\n它不是在你体内悸动吗！？",
    "Town": "小镇",
    "You defeated the corrupted priest? \n\nThen the temple may be safe again. \n\nThank you.": "你打败了腐化祭司？\n\n然后圣殿可能会再次安全。\n\n谢谢。",
