    "\"And I ask, and I ask, and I ask again!\"  The Priest's voice rings out.\nYou see no one else in the chamber, but the sound seems to come from everywhere at once, calling back.\n\"And we answer, and we answer, and we answer again!\"\n\"And who do I ask, and who do I ask!?\"  The Priest's voice crescendos.\nBefore the formless can respond, the Priest sees you and raises his baton.\n\"And on this day we see a stranger!\"  He points the baton at you, and the sound of the hymns intensifies.\nHis stage presence dissipates and he whispers, \"I just handle the music, please, let me live.\"\nHe looks terrified, but ready to defend himself.": "“而我问，我问，我再问！”祭司的声音回荡开来。\n\n你看不见密室中有其他人，但那声音仿佛同时从四面八方传来，回响着。\n\n“而我们答，我们答，我们再次回答！”\n\n“而我在问谁，我在问谁！？”祭司的声音愈加强烈。\n\n在无形者回应之前，祭司看见了你，举起了他的指挥棒。\n\n“而在这日，我们看见了一个异乡人！”他用指挥棒指向你，圣歌的声音愈加强烈。\n\n他的舞台气场骤然消散，低声说：“我只是负责音乐的，求你了，让我活着。”\n\n他看上去惊恐万分，但已准备好自卫。",

